---
const pillars = [
  {
    title: 'Concierge-first support',
    description:
      'You get direct, human guidance on pacing, lighting, and launch rituals without agency strings attached.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Only the essentials',
    description:
      'We trimmed the page to the key moves so you can scan on mobile, decide, and keep momentum toward signup.'
  },
  {
    title: 'StartRight as your base',
    description:
      'Claim the kit once you join and unlock curated scripts, checklists, and room setups tailored to your comfort level.'
  }
];
---
<section class="border-y border-white/5 bg-black/30 px-6 py-16">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl space-y-10">
    <div class="space-y-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-[clamp(0.75rem,1.1vw,0.9rem)] uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-rose-petal/70">
        Why cam with us
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,2.8rem)] text-white">Concierge energy, minimal noise</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-[clamp(0.95rem,1.7vw,1.1rem)] text-white/70">
        We keep the homepage lean and focus on the decisions that matter: picking a platform, proving signup, and unlocking the kit
        that helps you run your room with confidence.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      {pillars.map((pillar) => (
        <article class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6 shadow-glow">
          <h3 class="font-display text-[clamp(1.3rem,3vw,1.7rem)] text-white">{pillar.title}</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-[clamp(0.95rem,1.6vw,1.05rem)] leading-relaxed text-white/75">{pillar.description}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
